==English==

===Intransitive verb===
'''[[buckle]] [[down]]'''
#{{idiom}} To put forth the needed [[effort]]; to [[focus]]; become serious; [[apply]] oneself (e.g. to work or study).
#:''If he would '''buckle down''' and do his homework, he could be an excellent student.''

